  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15047">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      <b>Radiation.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15047 mb-requirement-id-15048">
        (a) Explain radiation and the difference between ionizing and
        nonionizing radiation. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/FrVUJ2c_Rwc?si=3e61M3Jbgg9w3ToV"
          target="_blank"
          >Radiation &amp; You (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/uJ3ea9fa6CA?si=lpSg7dn3koa5wAOV"
          target="_blank"
          >IDTIMWYTIM: Radiation (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15047 mb-requirement-id-15049">
        (b) Explain the ALARA principle. Explain what process you would go
        through to ensure your dose is kept ALARA when performing the
        requirements in this merit badge. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.cdc.gov/radiation-health/safety/alara.html"
          target="_blank"
        >
          The ALARA Principle (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15047 mb-requirement-id-15050">
        (c) Describe the radiation hazard symbol and explain where it should be
        used. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Nss1nl56fPo?si=gjiyC4gVAGL9CMsk"
          target="_blank"
          >Radiation Hazard Symbol (video)</a
        >
        <br />
        <a
          href="https://www.iaea.org/newscenter/news/how-are-universal-ionizing-radiation-symbols-used-around-the-world/"
          target="_blank"
          >How Are Universal Ionizing Radiation Symbols Used Around the World?
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15047 mb-requirement-id-15051">
        (d) Explain how we are exposed to ionizing radiation from outside the
        earth as well as on earth every day. List four examples of Naturally
        Occurring Radioactive Materials (NORM) that are in your house or grocery
        store and explain why they are radioactive. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/-9gD6FMivTQ?si=O-BCuqRKLgTMGZpg"
          target="_blank"
          >Five Radioactive Products We Use Every Day (video)</a
