  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15053">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      <b>Basic Nuclear Science.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15053 mb-requirement-id-15054">
        (a) Explain the following terms: atom, nucleus, proton, neutron,
        electron, quark, isotope; alpha particle, beta particle, gamma ray,
        X-ray; ionization, radioactivity, radioisotope, and stability. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://nplab.webspace.durham.ac.uk/glossary/" target="_blank"
          >Glossary of Nuclear Science Terms (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/faB9Gb7bl9I?si=Et7Yi1cp8zLvyppP"
          target="_blank"
          >What Are Isotopes? (video)</a
        >
        <br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/LraNu_78sCw?si=o4zrlNUwhUT69eB6"
          target="_blank"
          >Quarks Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15053 mb-requirement-id-15055">
        (b) Choose an element from the periodic table. Construct 3-D models for
        the atoms of three isotopes of this element, showing neutrons, protons,
        and electrons. Write down the isotope notation for each model including
        the atomic and mass numbers. In a separate model or diagram, explain or
        show how quarks make up protons and neutrons. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Nuclear%20Science/Isotope%20Model%20Activity.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Make a Model of an Isotope (PDF)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://isotopes.ans.org/" target="_blank"
          >Interactive Isotopes (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15056">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      <b>Modern Particle Physics.</b>
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15056 mb-requirement-id-15057">
        (a) Explain how a particle accelerator works. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/vIeRLeQq7V4?si=wf3TBAQxCGd1nYA5"
          target="_blank"
          >Particle Accelerators: What Are They, How Do They Work and Why Are
          They Important To Us? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15056 mb-requirement-id-15058">
        (b) Do ONE of the following: <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/N3i6CgUHSoc?si=tXJzA1pfqwIYRlXE"
          target="_blank"
          >Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory Nuclear Science Division
