  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15063">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      <b>Radiation Safety.</b> Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15063 mb-requirement-id-15064">
        (a) Using a radiation survey meter and a radioactive source, show how
        the counts per minute change as the source gets closer to or farther
        from the radiation detector. Place three different materials between the
        source and the detector, then explain any differences in the
        measurements per minute. Explain how time, distance, and shielding can
        reduce an individual's radiation dose. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Nuclear%20Science/shutterstock_1169023357.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >How Materials Shield Radiation (PDF)</a
        >
        <br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/bNSKIbRNy3c?si=3WqSseNb_EbOeZAx"
          target="_blank"
          >Time, Distance and Shielding (video)</a
        >
        <br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/GdZD_hJBdOE?si=p4mOulsJpBxDWH5j"
          target="_blank"
          >Measuring Radiation (video)</a
        >
        <br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/0-Yaeh3dOZk?si=Z1MokzEOznMdvlZD"
          target="_blank"
          >Using a Survey Meter: CPM vs Distance (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15063 mb-requirement-id-15065">
        (b) Describe how radon is detected in homes. Discuss the steps taken for
        the long-term and short-term test methods, tell how to interpret the
        results, and explain when each type of test should be used. Explain the
        health concerns related to radon gas and tell what steps can be taken to
        reduce radon in buildings. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/24aoot_CwoM?si=IYOyLpbVk2z2fb4R"
          target="_blank"
          >What is Radon, Anyway? (video)</a
        >
        <br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/SlRVdKdTBFE?si=pJrBWumWDON3uPcG"
          target="_blank"
          >How Dangerous Is Radon to Your Health? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15063 mb-requirement-id-15066">
        (c) Visit a place where X-rays are used. Draw a floor plan of this room.
        Show where the unit, the unit operator, and the patient would be when
        the X-ray unit is operated. Explain the precautions taken and the
        importance of those precautions for the safety of the operator. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/-pwY3-7lJJg?si=qctALb5U-IM9vG-K"
          target="_blank"
          >X-Ray Room Tour || Ask the Rad Tech (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
